## 10. Common Patterns

### 10.1 Conditional Features Based on Environment

```typescript
import { env, isProduction } from '@/shared/config/env'

if (!isProduction) {
  // Enable dev tools only in development
  import('./devtools').then((module) => module.setupDevtools())
}
```

---

### 10.2 Environment-Specific API URLs

```typescript
import { env } from '@/shared/config/env'

const client = createClient({
  url: env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL,
  requestPolicy: env.EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ENV === 'development' ? 'network-only' : 'cache-first',
})
```

---

## 11. Debugging Configuration Issues

### 11.1 Check Loaded Environment

```typescript
import Constants from 'expo-constants'

console.log('Expo Config:', Constants.expoConfig)
console.log('Manifest:', Constants.manifest)
```

---

### 11.2 Verify Environment Variables

Add to `App.tsx` (development only):

```typescript
if (__DEV__) {
  console.log('Environment:', {
    API_URL: process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL,
    APP_ENV: process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ENV,
  })
}
```

