## 12. Migration Checklist (For New Projects)

- [ ] Create `app.config.ts` (not `app.json`)
- [ ] Create `.env.example` (commit to repo)
- [ ] Create `.env.development` (do NOT commit)
- [ ] Create `.env.production` (do NOT commit)
- [ ] Add `.env.*` to `.gitignore` (except `.env.example`)
- [ ] Create `src/shared/config/env.schema.ts` (Zod schema)
- [ ] Create `src/shared/config/env.ts` (validated export)
- [ ] Update `eas.json` with build profiles
- [ ] Document required env vars in README
- [ ] Set EAS Secrets for sensitive values

---

## 13. Security Checklist

- [ ] No secrets in `.env` files committed to repo
- [ ] All `.env` files ignored in `.gitignore`
- [ ] Sensitive values use EAS Secrets
- [ ] Environment schema validates at build time
- [ ] No API keys, tokens, or passwords in source code
- [ ] Different bundle IDs for dev/production (prevents overwriting)

---

## 14. Forbidden Patterns

❌ **DO NOT:**

- Commit `.env` files with real values to version control
- Hardcode API URLs directly in code
- Store secrets in `app.config.ts` or any source file
- Use environment variables without the `EXPO_PUBLIC_` prefix (client-side)
- Skip validation (always use Zod schema)
- Guess at environment variable names (document in `.env.example`)

---

## 15. Summary

**Configuration Flow:**

1. Define env vars in `.env.development` / `.env.production`
2. Create Zod schema in `env.schema.ts`
3. Validate and export in `env.ts`
4. Import type-safe `env` object throughout app
5. Use EAS Secrets for sensitive values
6. Configure build profiles in `eas.json`

**Result:**
- Type-safe config access
- Build-time validation (fail fast)
- No secrets in repo
- Clear documentation
- Environment-specific builds

